wwpLeosFlowMIB.name: wwpLeosFlowMIB

revisions.description: Added new objects to support Ipv6 rate limits wwpLeosFlowCpuRateLimitIpV6Mgmt, wwpLeosFlowCpuRateLimitStatsIpV6MgmtPassed, wwpLeosFlowCpuRateLimitStatsIpV6MgmtDropped, wwpLeosFlowCpuRateLimitInet6, wwpLeosFlowCpuRateLimitStatsInet6Passed, wwpLeosFlowCpuRateLimitStatsInet6Dropped .
Added RAPS Frame Type into CpuRateLimit related MIB objects
Added the Port Service Level table and the ability to set secondary queue sizes for service levels.

wwpLeosFlowMIB.contactinfo: Mib Meister 115 North Sullivan Road Spokane Valley, WA 99037 USA Phone: +1 509 242 9000 Email: support@ciena.com
wwpLeosFlowMIB.description: MIB module for the WWP FLOW specific information. This MIB module is common between 4.x and 6.x platforms.

PriorityMapping.name: PriorityMapping
PriorityMapping.description: Represents the priority mapping. Octets in this object represents the remarked priority values for priority 0-7 respectively.

wwpLeosFlowAgeTime.name: wwpLeosFlowAgeTime
wwpLeosFlowAgeTime.description: Specifies the age time after which mac entries will be flushed out.

wwpLeosFlowAgeTimeState.name: wwpLeosFlowAgeTimeState
wwpLeosFlowAgeTimeState.description: Specifies if age time is enabled or disabled.

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelTable.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelTable
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelTable.description: A table of flow service level entries. Following criteria must be met while creating entry in the table. - All indexes must be specified - wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelCirBW and wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPirBW must be set. - wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelStatus must be set to create and go.

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelEntry
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelEntry.description: The flow service level entry in the Table.

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelDirection.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelDirection
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelDirection.description: Service level Id direction used as index in the service level entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPort.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPort
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPort.description: Port id used as index in the service level entry. If it is intended to not specify the port id in the index, this value should be set to 0.

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelId.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelId
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelId.description: Service level Id used as index in the service level entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelName.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelName
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelName.description: The flow service level name associated with this service level.

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPriority.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPriority
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPriority.description: The internal traffic-queue priority. This may also be used as a weighting factor.

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelQueueSize.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelQueueSize
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelQueueSize.description: The size of the traffic queue provisioned for this service level entry. This may also be referred to as Latency Tolerance.

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelDropEligibility.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelDropEligibility
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelDropEligibility.description: This item is used to indicate whether or not frames should be dropped or queued when frame buffer resources become scarce.

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelShareEligibility.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelShareEligibility
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelShareEligibility.description: This item is used to indicate whether or not a service level may be shared among entries in the flow service-mapping table.

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelCirBW.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelCirBW
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelCirBW.description: The committed information rate (bandwidth) in Kbps associated with this service level entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPirBW.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPirBW
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPirBW.description: The peak information rate (maximum bandwidth) in Kbps associated with this service level entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceStatus.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceStatus
wwpLeosFlowServiceStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. In particular, a newly created row cannot be made active until one of the following instances have been set: - wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelCirBW - wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPirBW.

wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveId.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveId
wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveId.description: This object is used to specifies the red curve index to be used for the given service level. If this OID is not specified, the system will use the default value of this object which is dependent on the queue size wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelQueueSize

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelQueueSizeYellow.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelQueueSizeYellow
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelQueueSizeYellow.description: The size of the yellow traffic queue provisioned for this service level entry. Also known as the discard preferred queue size.

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelQueueSizeRed.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelQueueSizeRed
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelQueueSizeRed.description: The size of the red traffic queue provisioned for this service level entry. Also known as the discard wanted queue size

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelFlowGroup.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelFlowGroup
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelFlowGroup.description: Service level Id direction used as index in the service level entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingTable.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingTable
wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingTable.description: A service mapping entry in the service-mapping table. To create entry in this table following criteria must be met and SNMP multiple set operation must be used to create entries. - wwpLeosFlowServiceMapDstSlidId must be set to valid SLID and this slid must exist on the device. Use wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelTable to create slid. - All indexes must be specified with exception to following objects. - wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingVid must be set to 0 if don't care else set it to some valid value. VID must exist on the device. - wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingSrcPort must be set to 0 if don't care else set it to some valid value. - wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingSrcTag must be set to 0 if don't care else set it to some valid value. - wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingDstPort must be set to 0 if don't care else set it to some valid value. - wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingDstTag must be set to 0 if don't care else set it to some valid value. - wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingProtocolType must be set to 1 if don't care else set it to some valid value. - wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingProtocolPortNum must be set to 0 if don't care else set it to some valid value. - wwpLeosFlowServiceMapSrcPri must be set to 255 if don't care else set it to some valid value.

wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingEntry
wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingEntry.description: A service mapping entry in the wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingTable.

wwpLeosFlowServiceMapVid.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceMapVid
wwpLeosFlowServiceMapVid.description: The VLAN id associated with this service mapping entry. If this object is set to 0, then this object should be ignored while creating the service-mapping entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceMapSrcPort.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceMapSrcPort
wwpLeosFlowServiceMapSrcPort.description: The source port id for the instance. This represents the ingress location of a flow. This port id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry. If this object is set to 0, then this object should be ignored while creating the service-mapping entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceMapSrcTag.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceMapSrcTag
wwpLeosFlowServiceMapSrcTag.description: The source VLAN tag associated with this service mapping entry. If this object is set to 0, then this object should be ignored while creating the service-mapping entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceMapDstPort.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceMapDstPort
wwpLeosFlowServiceMapDstPort.description: The destination port id for the instance. This represents the egress location for a flow. This port id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry. If this object is set to 0, then this object should be ignored while creating the service-mapping entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceMapDstTag.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceMapDstTag
wwpLeosFlowServiceMapDstTag.description: The destination VLAN tag associated with this service mapping entry. If this object is set to 0, then this object should be ignored while creating the service-mapping entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceMapSrcPri.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceMapSrcPri
wwpLeosFlowServiceMapSrcPri.description: The incoming packet vlan tag priority on the wwpLeosFlowServiceMapSrcPort. The 802.1p packet priority valid values are only from 0 to 7. If this object is set to 255 (or signed 8-bit integer -1), then this object should be ignored while creating the service-mapping entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceMapProtocolType.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceMapProtocolType
wwpLeosFlowServiceMapProtocolType.description: The Layer 4 protocol type used as index in the table. This will correspond to the TCP or UDP protocol. If this object is set to 1, then this object should be ignored while creating the service-mapping entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceMapProtocolPortNum.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceMapProtocolPortNum
wwpLeosFlowServiceMapProtocolPortNum.description: The Layer 4 protocol port number used as index in the table. This will correspond to a TCP or UDP port number. If this object is set to 0, then this object should be ignored while creating the service-mapping entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceMapDstSlidId.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceMapDstSlidId
wwpLeosFlowServiceMapDstSlidId.description: The service level id to apply to the flow at egress. If this object is set to 0, then this object should be ignored while creating the service-mapping entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceMapSrcSlidId.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceMapSrcSlidId
wwpLeosFlowServiceMapSrcSlidId.description: The service level id to apply to the flow at ingress. If this object is set to 0, then this object should be ignored while creating the service-mapping entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceMapPriRemarkStatus.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceMapPriRemarkStatus
wwpLeosFlowServiceMapPriRemarkStatus.description: Setting this object to 'true' will enable remarking of the VLAN tag priority for frames that match the classification defined by this service-mapping entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceMapRemarkPri.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceMapRemarkPri
wwpLeosFlowServiceMapRemarkPri.description: The remark priority value. For frames that match the classification defined by this service-mapping entry, the VLAN tag priority will be remarked with this value.

wwpLeosFlowServiceMapStatus.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceMapStatus
wwpLeosFlowServiceMapStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'.

wwpLeosFlowServiceACTable.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceACTable
wwpLeosFlowServiceACTable.description: A Table of FLOW Service Access Control Entries.

wwpLeosFlowServiceACEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceACEntry
wwpLeosFlowServiceACEntry.description: A service Access entry in the wwpLeosFlowServiceACTable.

wwpLeosFlowServiceACPortId.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceACPortId
wwpLeosFlowServiceACPortId.description: Port id for the instance. This port id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry. Used as index in service access table.

wwpLeosFlowServiceACVid.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceACVid
wwpLeosFlowServiceACVid.description: The VLAN id associated with this access control entry. Used as index in service access table. If the platform supports only port-based service access control, this value should be set to 0.

wwpLeosFlowServiceACMaxDynamicMacCount.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceACMaxDynamicMacCount
wwpLeosFlowServiceACMaxDynamicMacCount.description: The maximum number of dynamic MAC Addresses that will be learned and authorized by this access control entry. This value should default to 24.

wwpLeosFlowServiceACDynamicNonFilteredMa.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceACDynamicNonFilteredMacCount
wwpLeosFlowServiceACDynamicNonFilteredMa.description: The current number of non-filtered or authorized dynamic MAC addresses recorded in this access control entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceACDynamicFilteredMacCo.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceACDynamicFilteredMacCount
wwpLeosFlowServiceACDynamicFilteredMacCo.description: The current number of filtered or non-authorized dynamic MAC addresses recorded in this access control entry.

wwpLeosFlowServiceACStatus.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceACStatus
wwpLeosFlowServiceACStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'.

wwpLeosFlowServiceACForwardLearning.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceACForwardLearning
wwpLeosFlowServiceACForwardLearning.description: To specify whether or not unlearned frames are forwarded or dropped.

wwpLeosFlowStaticMacTable.name: wwpLeosFlowStaticMacTable
wwpLeosFlowStaticMacTable.description: The (conceptual) table to add the static mac addresses.

wwpLeosFlowStaticMacEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowStaticMacEntry
wwpLeosFlowStaticMacEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpLeosFlowStaticMacTable.

wwpLeosFlowSMVid.name: wwpLeosFlowSMVid
wwpLeosFlowSMVid.description: The service network id associated with this entry. Used as index in static MAC table.

wwpLeosFlowSMMacAddr.name: wwpLeosFlowSMMacAddr
wwpLeosFlowSMMacAddr.description: A unicast MAC address to be statically configured. Used as index in static MAC table.

wwpLeosFlowSMPortId.name: wwpLeosFlowSMPortId
wwpLeosFlowSMPortId.description: Port id for the static MAC instance. This port id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpLeosFlowSMTag.name: wwpLeosFlowSMTag
wwpLeosFlowSMTag.description: The VLAN tag for this static MAC instance.

wwpLeosFlowSMStatus.name: wwpLeosFlowSMStatus
wwpLeosFlowSMStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'. In particular, a newly created row cannot be made active until the corresponding instances of wwpLeosFlowSMPortId and wwpLeosFlowSMTag have been set. The following objects may not be modified while the value of this object is active(1): - wwpLeosFlowSMPortId - wwpLeosFlowSMTag

wwpLeosFlowLearnTable.name: wwpLeosFlowLearnTable
wwpLeosFlowLearnTable.description: A Table of flow learn entries.

wwpLeosFlowLearnEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowLearnEntry
wwpLeosFlowLearnEntry.description: A flow learn entry in the wwpLeosFlowLearnTable.

wwpLeosFlowLearnVid.name: wwpLeosFlowLearnVid
wwpLeosFlowLearnVid.description: The VLAN id associated with this flow-learn entry.

wwpLeosFlowLearnAddr.name: wwpLeosFlowLearnAddr
wwpLeosFlowLearnAddr.description: The address associated with this flow learn entry. Address can be layer 2 mac address or layer 3 ip address. If address is layer 3 ip address then first two bytes will be 0.

wwpLeosFlowLearnSrcPort.name: wwpLeosFlowLearnSrcPort
wwpLeosFlowLearnSrcPort.description: Source port Id for the instance. This port Id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpLeosFlowLearnSrcTag.name: wwpLeosFlowLearnSrcTag
wwpLeosFlowLearnSrcTag.description: The source VLAN tag associated with this flow-learn entry.

wwpLeosFlowLearnSrcPri.name: wwpLeosFlowLearnSrcPri
wwpLeosFlowLearnSrcPri.description: The source Layer 2 priority associated with this flow-learn entry.

wwpLeosFlowLearnAddrType.name: wwpLeosFlowLearnAddrType
wwpLeosFlowLearnAddrType.description: The address type associated with this flow-learn entry. Address can be layer 2 type or layer 3 type.

wwpLeosFlowLearnDstPort.name: wwpLeosFlowLearnDstPort
wwpLeosFlowLearnDstPort.description: Destination port id associated with this flow-learn entry. This port id should refer to the dot1dBasePort in the Dot1dBasePortEntry.

wwpLeosFlowLearnDstTag.name: wwpLeosFlowLearnDstTag
wwpLeosFlowLearnDstTag.description: The destination VLAN tag associated with this flow-learn entry.

wwpLeosFlowLearnType.name: wwpLeosFlowLearnType
wwpLeosFlowLearnType.description: The flow-learn entry type. This indicates whether or not the device was learned dynamically or entered as a static MAC.

wwpLeosFlowLearnIsFiltered.name: wwpLeosFlowLearnIsFiltered
wwpLeosFlowLearnIsFiltered.description: This value indicates whether or not the flow-learn entry is filtered. A value of 'true' indicates the flow-learn entry is filtered.

wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsTable.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsTable
wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsTable.description: A Table of flow service statistics entries.

wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsEntry
wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsEntry.description: A flow service statistics entry in the wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsTable.

wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsRxHi.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsRxHi
wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsRxHi.description: The number of bytes received for this flow service entry. This counter represents the upper 32 bits of the counter value.

wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsRxLo.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsRxLo
wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsRxLo.description: The number of bytes received for this flow service entry. This counter represents the lower 32 bits of the counter value.

wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsTxHi.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsTxHi
wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsTxHi.description: The number of bytes transmitted for this flow service entry. This counter represents the upper 32 bits of the counter value.

wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsTxLo.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsTxLo
wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsTxLo.description: The number of bytes transmitted for this flow service entry. This counter represents the lower 32 bits of the counter value.

wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsType.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsType
wwpLeosFlowServiceStatsType.description: Specifies the type of statistics for given entry.

wwpLeosFlowMacFindTable.name: wwpLeosFlowMacFindTable
wwpLeosFlowMacFindTable.description: A flow MAC-find table. MAC address must be specified to walk through the MIB.

wwpLeosFlowMacFindEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowMacFindEntry
wwpLeosFlowMacFindEntry.description: A flow service MAC statistics table.

wwpLeosFlowMacFindMacAddr.name: wwpLeosFlowMacFindMacAddr
wwpLeosFlowMacFindMacAddr.description: This variable defines the mac address used as index in the MAC-find table.

wwpLeosFlowMacFindVlanId.name: wwpLeosFlowMacFindVlanId
wwpLeosFlowMacFindVlanId.description: The VLAN ID on which this MAC address is learned.

wwpLeosFlowMacFindPort.name: wwpLeosFlowMacFindPort
wwpLeosFlowMacFindPort.description: This specifies the port id on which this MAC address is learned.

wwpLeosFlowMacFindVlanTag.name: wwpLeosFlowMacFindVlanTag
wwpLeosFlowMacFindVlanTag.description: This specifies the VLAN tag on which this MAC address is learned.

wwpLeosFlowPriRemapTable.name: wwpLeosFlowPriRemapTable
wwpLeosFlowPriRemapTable.description: The (conceptual) table to add the static mac addresses.

wwpLeosFlowPriRemapEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowPriRemapEntry
wwpLeosFlowPriRemapEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the wwpLeosFlowStaticMacTable.

wwpLeosFlowUserPri.name: wwpLeosFlowUserPri
wwpLeosFlowUserPri.description: Specifies the user priority. Also used as index in the table.

wwpLeosFlowRemappedPri.name: wwpLeosFlowRemappedPri
wwpLeosFlowRemappedPri.description: Specifies the remapped priority for given 'wwpLeosFlowUserPri'.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingTable.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingTable
wwpLeosFlowSMappingTable.description: A service mapping entry in the service-mapping table. To create entry in this table following criteria must be met. - The indexes to the service mapping entry consist of type-value pairs. - There are four(4) sections to the entry. -- NETWORK (type / value) -- SOURCE (type / value) -- DESTINATION (type / value) -- CLASS OF SERVICE (type / value) - All indexes must be specified with the appropriate enumerated - type. If the TYPE is set to 'none', the corresponding VALUE - MUST be set to zero(0). - - The service-mapping entry is very generic. As such, acceptable - combinations of types and values will be scrutinized by the - running platform.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingEntry
wwpLeosFlowSMappingEntry.description: A service mapping entry in the wwpLeosFlowSMappingTable.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingNetType.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingNetType
wwpLeosFlowSMappingNetType.description: This object specifies the NETWORK object TYPE for the entry. - - If set to 'none', the corresponding value in - wwpLeosFlowSMappingNetValue MUST be zero(0). - - If set to vlan, a valid vlan-id must be specified. - If set to vsi, a valid ethernet virtual-switch-instance id must be specified. - If set to vsi_mpls, a valid mpls virtual-switch-instance id must be specified - - This used as index in the table.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingNetValue.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingNetValue
wwpLeosFlowSMappingNetValue.description: This object specifies the NETWORK object ID for the entry. - - This item must be set according to the value set - in wwpLeosFlowSMappingNetType. If wwpLeosFlowSMappingNetType - equals: - none(1): MUST be set to zero(0). - vlan(2): MUST be set to valid existing vlan id. - vsi(3): MUST be set to valid existing ethernet virtual switch id. - vsiMpls(4): MUST be set to valid existing mpls virtual switch id. - - This used as index in the table.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingSrcType.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingSrcType
wwpLeosFlowSMappingSrcType.description: This object specifies the SOURCE object TYPE for the entry. - - If set to 'none', the corresponding value in - wwpLeosFlowSMappingSrcValue MUST be zero(0). - - If set to port, a valid port group id must be specified. - If set to mplsVc, a valid mpls-virtual-circuit id must be specified. - - This used as index in the table.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingSrcValue.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingSrcValue
wwpLeosFlowSMappingSrcValue.description: This object specifies the SOURCE object ID for the entry. - - This item must be set according to the value set - in wwpLeosFlowSMappingSrcType. If wwpLeosFlowSMappingSrcType - equals: - none(1): MUST be set to zero(0). - port(2): MUST be set to valid existing port group id. - mplsVc(3): MUST be set to valid existing mpls-virtual-circuit id. - - This used as index in the table.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingDstType.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingDstType
wwpLeosFlowSMappingDstType.description: This object specifies the DESTINATION object TYPE for the entry. - - If set to 'none', the corresponding value in - wwpLeosFlowSMappingDstValue MUST be zero(0). - - If set to port, a valid port group id must be specified. - If set to mplsVc, a valid mpls-virtual-circuit id must be specified. - - This used as index in the table.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingDstValue.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingDstValue
wwpLeosFlowSMappingDstValue.description: This object specifies the DESTINATION object ID for the entry. - - This item must be set according to the value set - in wwpLeosFlowSMappingDstType. If wwpLeosFlowSMappingDstType - equals: - none(1): MUST be set to zero(0). - port(2): MUST be set to valid existing port group id. - mplsVc(3): MUST be set to valid existing mpls-virtual-circuit id. - - This used as index in the table.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingCosType.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingCosType
wwpLeosFlowSMappingCosType.description: This object specifies the CLASS OF SERVICE object TYPE for the entry. - - If set to 'none', the corresponding value in - wwpLeosFlowSMappingCosValue MUST be zero(0). - - If set to tcpSrcPort, tcpDstPort, udpSrcPort, or udpDstPort, - a valid, NON-ZERO tcp or udp port must be specified. - - If set to phb, a valid per-hop-behavior enumeration must be specified. - If set to dscp, a valid differentiated services code point must be specified. - If set to ipPrec, a valid ip-precedence must be specified. - If set to dot1dPri, a valid 802.1d/p priority must be specified. - If set to cvlan, a support Customer VLAN must be specified - - This used as index in the table.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingCosValue.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingCosValue
wwpLeosFlowSMappingCosValue.description: This object specifies the CLASS OF SERVICE object ID for the entry. - - This item must be set according to the value set - in wwpLeosFlowSMappingCosType. If wwpLeosFlowSMappingCosType - equals: - none(1): MUST be set to zero(0). - - phb(2): (1..13) - cs0(1),cs1(2),cs2(3),cs3(4),cs4(5),cs5(6),cs6(7),cs7(8), - af1(9),af2(10),af3(11),af4(12),ef(13) - - dscp(3): (0..63) - ipPrec(4): (0..7) - dot1dPri(5): (0..7) - mplsExp(6): (0..7) - - tcpSrcPort(7): (1..65535). - tcpDstPort(8): (1..65535). - udpSrcPort(9): (1..65535). - udpDstPort(10): (1..65535). - - cvlan(12): (1..4094) - - Depending on the platform, the COS type/value may be recognized for certain - frame tag-structures. For example, some platforms can recognize ipPrec, dscp - dot1dPri only for double-tagged frames. Some require untagged or single-tagged - frames to recognize TCP/UDP ports. Operator should consult the software - configuration guide for the specified product. - - This used as index in the table.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingDstSlid.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingDstSlid
wwpLeosFlowSMappingDstSlid.description: The service level id to apply to the flow at the destination point. Depending on the platform this object may or may not be set to 0 while creating the service-mapping entry. The corresponding destination-port and slid must exist in the service-level table.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingSrcSlid.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingSrcSlid
wwpLeosFlowSMappingSrcSlid.description: The service level ID to apply to the flow at the source-port. Depending on the platform this object may or may not be set to 0 while creating the service-mapping entry. The corresponding source-port and SLID must exist in the service-level table

wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatus.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatus
wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingRedCurveOffset.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingRedCurveOffset
wwpLeosFlowSMappingRedCurveOffset.description: This object specifies the red curve offset to be used for given service mapping. If this object is not set then the device will choose default red curve offset which is 0.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingCpuPort.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingCpuPort
wwpLeosFlowSMappingCpuPort.description: This object specifies if the CPU port is to be used as the src port.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsTable.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsTable
wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsTable.description: A Table of flow service statistics entries.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsEntry
wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsEntry.description: A flow service statistics entry in the wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsTable.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsRxHi.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsRxHi
wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsRxHi.description: The number of bytes received for this flow service entry. This counter represents the upper 32 bits of the counter value

wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsRxLo.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsRxLo
wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsRxLo.description: The number of bytes received for this flow service entry. This counter represents the lower 32 bits of the counter value.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsTxHi.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsTxHi
wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsTxHi.description: The number of bytes transmitted for this flow service entry. This counter represents the upper 32 bits of the counter value.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsTxLo.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsTxLo
wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsTxLo.description: The number of bytes transmitted for this flow service entry. This counter represents the lower 32 bits of the counter value.

wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsType.name: wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsType
wwpLeosFlowSMappingStatsType.description: Specifies the type of statistics for given entry.

wwpLeosFlowCosSync1dToExpTable.name: wwpLeosFlowCosSync1dToExpTable
wwpLeosFlowCosSync1dToExpTable.description: A table of flow cos sync 1d to exp entries. Entries cannot be created or destroyed.

wwpLeosFlowCosSync1dToExpEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowCosSync1dToExpEntry
wwpLeosFlowCosSync1dToExpEntry.description: A flow cos sync 1d to 1d entry in the wwpLeosFlowCosSync1dToExpTable.

wwpLeosFlowCosSync1dToExpMapFrom.name: wwpLeosFlowCosSync1dToExpMapFrom
wwpLeosFlowCosSync1dToExpMapFrom.description: This object is used as index in the table and represents cos 1d priority. Any frame coming in with this priority will be synchronized with priority specified by wwpLeosFlowCosSync1dToExpMapTo.

wwpLeosFlowCosSync1dToExpMapTo.name: wwpLeosFlowCosSync1dToExpMapTo
wwpLeosFlowCosSync1dToExpMapTo.description: This object specifies the remapped exp value of the frame which ingresses with dot1d priority of wwpLeosFlowCosSync1dToExpMapFrom.

wwpLeosFlowCosSyncExpTo1dTable.name: wwpLeosFlowCosSyncExpTo1dTable
wwpLeosFlowCosSyncExpTo1dTable.description: A table of flow cos sync 1d to exp entries.

wwpLeosFlowCosSyncExpTo1dEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowCosSyncExpTo1dEntry
wwpLeosFlowCosSyncExpTo1dEntry.description: A flow cos sync 1d to 1d entry in the wwpLeosFlowCosSyncExpTo1dTable.

wwpLeosFlowCosSyncExpTo1dMapFrom.name: wwpLeosFlowCosSyncExpTo1dMapFrom
wwpLeosFlowCosSyncExpTo1dMapFrom.description: This object is used as index in the table and represents cos 1d priority. Any frame coming in with this priority will be synchronized with priority specified by wwpLeosFlowCosSyncExpTo1dMapTo.

wwpLeosFlowCosSyncExpTo1dMapTo.name: wwpLeosFlowCosSyncExpTo1dMapTo
wwpLeosFlowCosSyncExpTo1dMapTo.description: This object specifies the remapped exp value of the frame which ingresses with dot1d priority of wwpLeosFlowCosSyncExpTo1dMapFrom.

wwpLeosFlowCosSyncIpPrecTo1dTable.name: wwpLeosFlowCosSyncIpPrecTo1dTable
wwpLeosFlowCosSyncIpPrecTo1dTable.description: A table of flow cos sync IP precedence to 1d entries.

wwpLeosFlowCosSyncIpPrecTo1dEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowCosSyncIpPrecTo1dEntry
wwpLeosFlowCosSyncIpPrecTo1dEntry.description: A flow cos sync Ip Precedence to 1d entry in the wwpLeosFlowCosSyncIpPrecTo1dTable.

wwpLeosFlowCosSyncIpPrecTo1dMapFrom.name: wwpLeosFlowCosSyncIpPrecTo1dMapFrom
wwpLeosFlowCosSyncIpPrecTo1dMapFrom.description: This object is used as index in the table and represents ip precedence value. Any frame coming in with wwpLeosFlowCosSyncIpPrecTo1dMapFrom IP precedence will be synchronized with dot1d specified by wwpLeosFlowCosSyncIpPrecTo1dMapTo.

wwpLeosFlowCosSyncIpPrecTo1dMapTo.name: wwpLeosFlowCosSyncIpPrecTo1dMapTo
wwpLeosFlowCosSyncIpPrecTo1dMapTo.description: This object specifies the ip precedence value to synchronize with when the frame ingresses with ip precedence value of wwpLeosFlowCosSyncIpPrecTo1dMapFrom.

wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dTable.name: wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dTable
wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dTable.description: A table of flow cos sync standard per hop behavior to 1d or Exp entries.

wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dEntry
wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dEntry.description: A flow cos sync standard per hop behavior to 1d entry in the wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dTable.

wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dMapFrom.name: wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dMapFrom
wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dMapFrom.description: This object is used as index in the table and represents AFx or EF value. Any frame coming in with wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dMapFrom AFx or EF value will be synchronized with dot1d priority specified by wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dMapTo. If wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dValue is not specified then no synchronization will happen.

wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dMapTo.name: wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dMapTo
wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dMapTo.description: This object specifies the AFx or EF dscp value to synchronize with when the frame ingresses with AFx or EF dscp value of wwpLeosFlowCosSyncDscpTo1dMapTo.

wwpLeosFlowL2SacTable.name: wwpLeosFlowL2SacTable
wwpLeosFlowL2SacTable.description: A table of flow l2 sac table.

wwpLeosFlowL2SacEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowL2SacEntry
wwpLeosFlowL2SacEntry.description: Represents each entry in the l2 Sac Table

wwpLeosFlowL2SacPortId.name: wwpLeosFlowL2SacPortId
wwpLeosFlowL2SacPortId.description: This mib object is index in the table. If port is not involved in L2 SAC then set this value to 0. 0 represents don't care.

wwpLeosFlowL2SacNetType.name: wwpLeosFlowL2SacNetType
wwpLeosFlowL2SacNetType.description: This mib object is used as index in the table. This object specifies how wwpLeosFlowSacValue should be interpreted. If this object is set to none then the wwpLeosFlowSacValue must be set to 0.

wwpLeosFlowSacNetValue.name: wwpLeosFlowSacNetValue
wwpLeosFlowSacNetValue.description: This mib object is used as index in the table. This object is only meaningful if wwpLeosFlowL2SacNetType is not set to none.

wwpLeosFlowL2SacLimit.name: wwpLeosFlowL2SacLimit
wwpLeosFlowL2SacLimit.description: This mib object specifies the l2 SAC limit. Device will not learn any mac greater than the limit specified by this object.

wwpLeosFlowL2SacCurMac.name: wwpLeosFlowL2SacCurMac
wwpLeosFlowL2SacCurMac.description: This mib object specifies the current mac count for the given l2 SAC entry.

wwpLeosFlowL2SacCurFilteredMac.name: wwpLeosFlowL2SacCurFilteredMac
wwpLeosFlowL2SacCurFilteredMac.description: This mib object specifies the current number of filtered macs for the given l2 SAC entry.

wwpLeosFlowL2SacOperState.name: wwpLeosFlowL2SacOperState
wwpLeosFlowL2SacOperState.description: This mib object specifies the current operation state for the given l2 SAC entry.

wwpLeosFlowL2SacRowStatus.name: wwpLeosFlowL2SacRowStatus
wwpLeosFlowL2SacRowStatus.description: Used to manage the creation and deletion of the conceptual rows in this table. To create a row in this table, a manager must set this object to 'createAndGo'.

wwpLeosFlowL2SacTrapState.name: wwpLeosFlowL2SacTrapState
wwpLeosFlowL2SacTrapState.description: Specifies if device should send L2 sac traps.

wwpLeosFlowStrictQueuingState.name: wwpLeosFlowStrictQueuingState
wwpLeosFlowStrictQueuingState.description: Specifies if device should adjust queues to support strict queuing.

wwpLeosFlowBwCalcMode.name: wwpLeosFlowBwCalcMode
wwpLeosFlowBwCalcMode.description: Specifies if the device should operate in transport or payload mode. In transport mode the frame length of an Ethernet frame used in measuring CIR will be from IFG through FCS. In payload mode the frame length of an Ethernet frame used in measuring CIR will be from the MAC DA through FCS.

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelFlowGroupState.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelFlowGroupState
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelFlowGroupState.description: This object specifies the current state of service level flow groups.

wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingCosRedMappingSt.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingCosRedMappingState
wwpLeosFlowServiceMappingCosRedMappingSt.description: This object specifies the current state of service mapping dot1d to Red offset mapping table(wwpLeosFlowCos1dToRedCurveOffsetTable). If this object is set to disable then wwpLeosFlowCos1dToRedCurveOffsetTable will not be used for dot1d to red offset mapping else it will be used.

wwpLeosFlowServiceAllRedCurveUnset.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceAllRedCurveUnset
wwpLeosFlowServiceAllRedCurveUnset.description: Setting this object to true will reset all the red curves in wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveTable table to factory default settings.

wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveTable.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveTable
wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveTable.description: A table to configure flow service red curve table.

wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveEntry
wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveEntry.description: Represents each entry in the flow service RED curve table.

wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveIndex.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveIndex
wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveIndex.description: This object is used as index in the red curve table.

wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveName.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveName
wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveName.description: This object specifies the name of the red curve.

wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveState.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveState
wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveState.description: This object specifies the current state of the red curve. This object can be set to enable or disable.

wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveMinThreshold.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveMinThreshold
wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveMinThreshold.description: This represents the minimum threshold in KBytes. When the queue length associated with this service reaches this number, RED begins to drop packets matching this Service-Mappings traffic classification. The valid range is between 0 and 65535 Kbytes. The actual number varies depending on the platform.

wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveMaxThreshold.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveMaxThreshold
wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveMaxThreshold.description: This represents the maximum threshold in KBytes. When the queue length associated with this service reaches this number, RED drops packets matching this Service-Mappings traffic classification at the rate specified in wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveDropProbability.

wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveDropProbabilit.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveDropProbability
wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveDropProbabilit.description: This object specifies the drop probability of a packet (matching this Service-Mapping classification) of being dropped when the queue length associated with this Service-Level reaches the value configured in wwpLeosFlowServiceMaxThreshold. The value represents a percentage (0-100).

wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveUnset.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveUnset
wwpLeosFlowServiceRedCurveUnset.description: Setting this object to true will reset the red curve settings to factory defaults.

wwpLeosFlowCos1dToRedCurveOffsetTable.name: wwpLeosFlowCos1dToRedCurveOffsetTable
wwpLeosFlowCos1dToRedCurveOffsetTable.description: A table of flow cos 1d to red curve offset entries.

wwpLeosFlowCos1dToRedCurveOffsetEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowCos1dToRedCurveOffsetEntry
wwpLeosFlowCos1dToRedCurveOffsetEntry.description: A table entry of flow cos 1d to red curve offset.

wwpLeosFlowCos1dToRedCurveOffset1dValue.name: wwpLeosFlowCos1dToRedCurveOffset1dValue
wwpLeosFlowCos1dToRedCurveOffset1dValue.description: This object is used as index in the table and represents cos 1d priority. Any frame coming in with this priority will be mapped to red cos offset value specified by wwpLeosFlowCos1dToRedCurveOffsetValue.

wwpLeosFlowCos1dToRedCurveOffsetValue.name: wwpLeosFlowCos1dToRedCurveOffsetValue
wwpLeosFlowCos1dToRedCurveOffsetValue.description: This object specifies the red curve offset value to be used when frame which ingresses with dot1d priority specified by wwpLeosFlowCos1dToRedCurveOffset1dValue.

wwpLeosFlowCosMapPCPTo1dTable.name: wwpLeosFlowCosMapPCPTo1dTable
wwpLeosFlowCosMapPCPTo1dTable.description: A table of flow cos mapping of PCP to .1d Pri.

wwpLeosFlowCosMapPCPTo1dEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowCosMapPCPTo1dEntry
wwpLeosFlowCosMapPCPTo1dEntry.description: A flow cos sync standard per hop behavior to 1d entry in the wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dTable.

wwpLeosFlowCosMapPCPTo1dMapFrom.name: wwpLeosFlowCosMapPCPTo1dMapFrom
wwpLeosFlowCosMapPCPTo1dMapFrom.description: This object is used as index in the table and represents PCP priority. Any frame coming in with wwpLeosFlowCosMapPCPTo1dMapFrom priority will be mapped to .1d priority specified by wwpLeosFlowCosMapPCPTo1dMapTo.

wwpLeosFlowCosMapPCPTo1dMapTo.name: wwpLeosFlowCosMapPCPTo1dMapTo
wwpLeosFlowCosMapPCPTo1dMapTo.description: This object specifies the .1d priority to map with when the frame ingresses with PCP priority specified by wwpLeosFlowCosMapPCPTo1dMapFrom.

wwpLeosFlowCosMap1dToPCPTable.name: wwpLeosFlowCosMap1dToPCPTable
wwpLeosFlowCosMap1dToPCPTable.description: A table of flow cos mapping of PCP to .1d Pri.

wwpLeosFlowCosMap1dToPCPEntry.name: wwpLeosFlowCosMap1dToPCPEntry
wwpLeosFlowCosMap1dToPCPEntry.description: A flow cos sync standard per hop behavior to 1d entry in the wwpLeosFlowCosSyncStdPhbTo1dTable.

wwpLeosFlowCosMap1dToPCPMapFrom.name: wwpLeosFlowCosMap1dToPCPMapFrom
wwpLeosFlowCosMap1dToPCPMapFrom.description: This object is used as index in the table and represents PCP priority. Any frame coming in with wwpLeosFlowCosMap1dToPCPMapFrom priority will be mapped to .1d priority specified by wwpLeosFlowCosMap1dToPCPMapTo.

wwpLeosFlowCosMap1dToPCPMapTo.name: wwpLeosFlowCosMap1dToPCPMapTo
wwpLeosFlowCosMap1dToPCPMapTo.description: This object specifies the .1d priority to map with when the frame ingresses with PCP priority specified by wwpLeosFlowCosMap1dToPCPMapFrom.

wwpLeosFlowMacMotionEventsEnable.name: wwpLeosFlowMacMotionEventsEnable
wwpLeosFlowMacMotionEventsEnable.description: Specifies whether MAC Motion traps and syslog messages will be generated when a MAC shifts from one port/vlan to another port/vlan.

wwpLeosFlowMacMotionEventsInterval.name: wwpLeosFlowMacMotionEventsInterval
wwpLeosFlowMacMotionEventsInterval.description: The minimum time in seconds that must elapse between each MAC Motion trap and syslog message that is generated.

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPortOverProvision.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPortOverProvisionedTrap
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPortOverProvision.description: A wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPortOverProvisionedTrap notification is sent when the provisioned bandwidth exceeds the total bandwidth available for a port. This situation may also occur when changes in a link aggregation group (such as deleting a port from the group) decrease the total bandwidth or at the bootTime when the link aggregation groups are formed.

wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPortUnderProvisio.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPortUnderProvisionedTrap
wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPortUnderProvisio.description: A wwpLeosFlowServiceLevelPortUnderProvisionedTrap notification is sent when the previously over-provisioned situation is resolved for a port.

wwpLeosFlowL2SacHighThreshold.name: wwpLeosFlowL2SacHighThreshold
wwpLeosFlowL2SacHighThreshold.description: A wwpLeosFlowL2SacHighThreshold notification is sent whenever Macs learned exceeds SAC threshold limit.

wwpLeosFlowL2SacNormalThreshold.name: wwpLeosFlowL2SacNormalThreshold
wwpLeosFlowL2SacNormalThreshold.description: A wwpLeosFlowL2SacNormalThreshold notification is sent whenever Macs learned gets back to normal after exceeding the SAC threshold limit.

wwpLeosFlowMacMotionNotification.name: wwpLeosFlowMacMotionNotification
wwpLeosFlowMacMotionNotification.description: A wwpLeosFlowMacMotionNotification is sent whenever a learned MAC moves from one port/vlan to a new port/vlan, at a rate defined by wwpLeosFlowMacMotionEventsInterval. The five objects returned by this trap are the MAC address that moved, the original port/vlan the MAC was learned on, and the new port/vlan the MAC has moved to.

wwpLeosFlowMacMotionAttrOldPort.name: wwpLeosFlowMacMotionAttrOldPort
wwpLeosFlowMacMotionAttrOldPort.description: The port number associated with the MAC that moved.

wwpLeosFlowMacMotionAttrOldVlan.name: wwpLeosFlowMacMotionAttrOldVlan
wwpLeosFlowMacMotionAttrOldVlan.description: The vlan number associated with the MAC that moved.

wwpLeosFlowMacMotionAttrNewPort.name: wwpLeosFlowMacMotionAttrNewPort
wwpLeosFlowMacMotionAttrNewPort.description: The port number associated with the MAC that moved.

wwpLeosFlowMacMotionAttrNewVlan.name: wwpLeosFlowMacMotionAttrNewVlan
wwpLeosFlowMacMotionAttrNewVlan.description: The vlan number associated with the MAC that moved.

wwpLeosFlowServiceTotalStatsTable.name: wwpLeosFlowServiceTotalStatsTable
wwpLeosFlowServiceTotalStatsTable.description: A table of flow service statistics entries.
